    {
      "id": "m9e83fb9",
      "questionNumber": 4,
      "questionText": "<p>Consider the following logic circuit.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9e80yi2/4c64871d-9847-4ec7-bab2-0cb1f0e4176e/b6c910a0-179d-11f0-9533-f7fd455b47a9/file-jaoe38c1m9e80yi3.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9e80yi2/4c64871d-9847-4ec7-bab2-0cb1f0e4176e/b6c910a0-179d-11f0-9533-f7fd455b47a9/file-jaoe38c1m9e80yi3.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 7th April Evening Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 26 English\">\n<p>The output is Y = 0 when :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>A = 1 and B = 0</p>",
        "<p>A = 0 and B = 0</p>",
        "<p>A = 1 and B = 1</p>",
        "<p>A = 0 and B = 1</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "digital-circuits",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9ksqa5v/5ffb9f16-3b00-462f-b307-5ad8eba9370d/61806430-1b3b-11f0-8234-eff1154e7d32/file-jaoe38c1m9ksqa5w.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9ksqa5v/5ffb9f16-3b00-462f-b307-5ad8eba9370d/61806430-1b3b-11f0-8234-eff1154e7d32/file-jaoe38c1m9ksqa5w.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 7th April Evening Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 26 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\mathrm{Y}_1=\\mathrm{A} \\cdot \\mathrm{~B}, \\mathrm{Y}_2=\\overline{\\mathrm{A}}+\\mathrm{B} \\\\\n&amp; \\mathrm{Y}=\\overline{\\mathrm{Y}_1 \\cdot \\mathrm{Y}_2}=\\overline{\\mathrm{Y}}_1+\\overline{\\mathrm{Y}}_2 \\\\\n&amp; \\mathrm{Y}=\\overline{\\mathrm{A} \\cdot \\mathrm{~B}}+\\overline{\\overline{\\mathrm{A}}+\\mathrm{B}} \\\\\n&amp; \\mathrm{Y}=\\overline{\\mathrm{A}}+\\overline{\\mathrm{B}}+\\mathrm{A} \\cdot \\overline{\\mathrm{~B}}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9ksrjik/4cbd4442-4950-4686-9d2e-a2a9fdb4612b/84890cc0-1b3b-11f0-8234-eff1154e7d32/file-jaoe38c1m9ksrjil.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9ksrjik/4cbd4442-4950-4686-9d2e-a2a9fdb4612b/84890cc0-1b3b-11f0-8234-eff1154e7d32/file-jaoe38c1m9ksrjil.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 7th April Evening Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 26 English Explanation 2\"></p>",
