    {
      "id": "PFM8bWZXLyl55GVp",
      "questionNumber": 5,
      "questionText": "For a common emitter configuration, if $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\beta $$ have their usual meanings, the incorrect relationship between $$\\alpha $$ and $$\\beta $$ is : ",
      "options": [
        "$$\\alpha  = {\\beta  \\over {1 + \\beta }}$$ ",
        "$$\\alpha  = {{{\\beta ^2}} \\over {1 + {\\beta ^2}}}$$ ",
        "$${1 \\over \\alpha } = {1 \\over \\beta } + 1$$ ",
        "$$\\alpha  = {\\beta  \\over {1 - {\\beta ^2}}}$$ "
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "transistors",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "We know, collector current is given as $${I_C} = \\beta {I_B}$$<br><br>\nAlso, $${I_C} = \\alpha {I_E}$$<br><br>\n​Using, $${I_E} = {I_B} + {I_C}$$<br><br>\n$${{{I_C}} \\over \\alpha } = {{{I_C}} \\over \\beta } + {I_C}$$<br><br>\nSolving above equations,<br><br>\n$${1 \\over \\alpha } = {1 \\over \\beta } + 1$$ <br><br>\n$$\\alpha  = {\\beta  \\over {1 + \\beta }}$$ ",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "mnswhx59",
      "questionNumber": 6,
      "questionText": "<p>For the given logic circuit, which of the following inputs combination will make both LED-1 and LED-2 to glow?</p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 4 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mnumvn4s/ee26259d-4c6f-4c4f-8158-d9abbf999418/5d9711c0-35cf-11f1-afe3-1d14009f2e59/file-6y3zli1mnumvn4t.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mnumvn4s/ee26259d-4c6f-4c4f-8158-d9abbf999418/5d9711c0-35cf-11f1-afe3-1d14009f2e59/file-6y3zli1mnumvn4t.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\">",
      "options": [
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{A}=0, \\mathrm{~B}=1, \\mathrm{C}=1 $$</p>\n",
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{A}=1, \\mathrm{~B}=0, \\mathrm{C}=0 $$</p>\n",
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{A}=1, \\mathrm{~B}=0, \\mathrm{C}=1 $$</p>\n",
        "<p>$$ \\mathrm{A}=1, \\mathrm{~B}=1, \\mathrm{C}=0 $$</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Physics",
      "topic": "digital-circuits",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 4 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mobtacfv/10730ec8-cb81-4312-b472-a371d16e3155/c04864b0-3f41-11f1-945b-a7f83dc9b71d/file-6y3zli1mobtacfw.webp?format=webp\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mobtacfv/10730ec8-cb81-4312-b472-a371d16e3155/c04864b0-3f41-11f1-945b-a7f83dc9b71d/file-6y3zli1mobtacfw.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$Y_1$ is the output of an OR gate whose inputs are $A$ and $B$,</p>\n<p>$$ Y_1=A+B $$</p>\n<p>$Y_2$ is an AND gate taking $Y_1$ and $C$ as input</p>\n<p>$$ Y_2=(A+B) \\cdot C $$</p>\n<p>$Y_3$ is an AND gate taking $Y_2$ and $A$ as input,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{gathered} Y_3=[(A+B) \\cdot C] \\cdot A \\\\ Y_3=A \\cdot(A+B) \\cdot C=A \\cdot C \\end{gathered} $$</p>\n<p>So, the truth table is,</p>\n<table>\n\n  <tbody><tr>\n\n    <th>A</th>\n\n    <th>B</th>\n\n    <th>C</th>\n\n    <th>Y<sub>1</sub> = A + B</th>\n\n    <th>Y<sub>2</sub> = (A + B) · C</th>\n\n    <th>Y<sub>3</sub> = A · C</th>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n    <td>0</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n    <td>1</td>\n\n  </tr>\n\n</tbody></table>\n<p>LED1 glows when $Y_1=1$ and LED2 glows when $Y_3=1$</p>\n<p>So for both the LEDs to glow we need $Y_1=1$ and $Y_3=1$</p>\n<p>From the table, this happens when:</p>\n<p>Since $\\mathrm{Y}_3=\\mathrm{A} \\cdot \\mathrm{C}$, so $\\mathrm{A}=1, \\mathrm{C}=1$</p>\n<p>And $\\mathrm{Y}_1$ will automatically be 1 because $\\mathrm{A}=1$</p>\n<p>Hence, the possible combinations are ( $A=1, B=0, C=1$ ) and ( $A=1, B=1, C=1$ ). </p>\n<p>Thus, the correct option is (C).</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "1lh249ef1",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "questionText": "<p>Name the logic gate equivalent to the diagram attached</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh300fpp/57300155-c704-4fa4-a153-fcc3749779a2/b17c4cc0-e71b-11ed-ab3e-bf3b57063390/file-1lh300fpq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh300fpp/57300155-c704-4fa4-a153-fcc3749779a2/b17c4cc0-e71b-11ed-ab3e-bf3b57063390/file-1lh300fpq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Physics - Semiconductor Question 64 English\"></p>",
      "options": [
        "NOR",
        "NAND",
        "AND",
